rst.com/popculture/top-100-songs-of-the-year/?year=2001|title=Top 100 Songs of 2001 - Billboard Year End Charts|website=Bobborst.com|accessdate=25 January 2019}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|59\n|}\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n!Chart (2002)\n!Position\n|-\n|Switzerland (Schweizer Hitparade)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hitparade.ch/charts/jahreshitparade/2002|title=Schweizer Jahreshitparade 2002 \u2013 hitparade.ch|publisher=Hung Medien|accessdate=24 January 2020}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|97\n|}\n\n===Decade-end charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n!Chart (2000\u20132009)\n!Position\n|-\n|Germany (Official German Charts)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rtl.de/fernsehprogramm/|title=RTL Fernsehprogramm von heute - aktuelles TV Programm|website=rtl.de}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|99\n|}\n\n===Certifications===\n{{certification Table Top}}\n{{certification Table Entry|region=Austria|type=single|award=Gold|title=Only Time|artist=Enya|relyear=2000}}\n{{certification Table Entry|region=Germany|type=single|award=Gold|number=3|title=Only Time|artist=Enya|relyear=2000}}\n{{certification Table Entry|region=Italy|type=single|award=Gold|title=Only Time|artist=Enya|relyear=2000|certyear=2019}}\n{{certification Table Entry|region=Switzerland|type=single|award=Gold|title=Only Time|artist=Enya|relyear=2000}}\n{{certification Table Bottom|streaming=true}}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Cover versions==\n*British soprano [[Keedie]] covered the song on her album ''[[I Believe My Heart]].''\n*The Chinese musical group [[Twelve Girls Band]] covered the song on their album ''[[Eastern Energy]].''\n*American singer [[Jackie Evancho]] covered the song during a live performance.{{citation needed|date=November 2013}}\n*Irish singer [[Brian McFadden]] covered the song on his fourth album ''[[The Irish Connection (Brian McFadden album)|The Irish Connection]].''\n*R\u00f3is\u00edn & Celtic Spirit also covered the song on the album ''The Magic of Enya.''\n*The American musical group [[Vitamin String Quartet]] covered the song on their album ''Dreams: The String Quartet Tribute to Enya.''\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of Billboard Adult Contemporary number ones of 2001]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{discogs master|27729|Only Time|type=single}}\n\n{{Enya songs}}\n\n[[Category:2000 singles]]\n[[Category:2001 singles]]\n[[Category:Enya songs]]\n[[Category:Canadian Singles Chart number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Germany]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Poland]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Switzerland]]\n[[Category:Billboard Adult Contemporary number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Billboard Adult Top 40 number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Pop ballads]]\n[[Category:Songs with lyrics by Roma Ryan]]\n[[Category:Songs with music by Enya]]\n[[Category:2000 songs]]\n[[Category:2000s ballads]]\n[[Category:Warner Music Group singles]]\n[[Category:Music memes]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|2000 single by Enya}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Only Time\n| cover      = Enya - Only Time cover.jpg\n| alt        =\n| caption    = Original release\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Enya]]\n| album      = [[A Day Without Rain]]\n| released   = 20 November 2000\n| format     =\n| recorded   = 2000\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[New-age music|New-age]]\n| length     =\n* 3:38 {{small|(album version)}}\n* 3:15 {{small|(S.A.F. pop radio remix)}}\n| label      = [[Warner Music Group|WEA]]\n| writer     =\n* Enya\n* [[Roma Ryan]]\n| producer   = [[Nicky Ryan]]\n| prev_title = [[Only If...]]\n| prev_year  = 1997\n| next_title = [[Wild Child (Enya song)|Wild Child]]\n| next_year  = 2001\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|7wfYIMyS_dI|\"Only Time\"}}}}\n}}\n\"'''Only Time'''\" is a song by Irish singer, songwriter and musician [[Enya]], released in November 2000 as the lead single to her fifth studio album, ''[[A Day Without Rain]]'' (2000). The song reached number one in Canada, Germany, Poland and Switzerland, number two in Austria, and became Enya's only top-ten single as a solo artist in the United States, peaking at number ten on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]. \n\n==Release==\nIn 2001, \"Only Time\" was released again as a [[remix]]. The track was remixed by the Swiss American Federation (S.A.F.) (Christian B. and Marc Dold) with a final remix by Enya's producer, [[Nicky Ryan]]. Enya donated the earnings from the sale of that single to the Uniform Firefighters Association's Widows' and Children's Fund to help the families of fire fighters in the aftermath of [[9/11]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://enya.sk/music/day-without-rain/only-time/|title=Only Time|publisher=}}</ref> The song was also featured in the soundtrack of the motion picture ''[[Sweet November (2001 film)|Sweet November]]''. Following the September 2001 attacks, sales of the album and its lead single, \"Only Time\", skyrocketed after it was used by several radio and television networks in their coverage and aftermath of the attacks. As a result, \"Only Time\" climbed to number ten on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] singles chart and number one on the [[Adult Contemporary (chart)|adult contemporary chart]].<ref name=\"billboard.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/adult-contemporary|title=Adult Contemporary Music Chart|website=Billboard}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/hot-100|title=Top 100 Songs - Billboard Hot 100 Chart|website=Billboard}}</ref>\n\nDuring the summer of 2001, [[NBC]] used the song in commercials to promote ''[[Friends]]'', which ended its season on a cliffhanger. NBC also used it as background during the death scene for character Bobby Caffey in the episode \"Unfinished Business\" (aired March 12, 2001) during the second season of ''[[Third Watch]]''. The exposure helped the song gain familiarity and increased radio play. As a result, the song became Enya's first top 40 radio hit in 12 years. The song appeared twice on the TV show ''[[Viva La Bam]]'' where it first appeared in the montage of [[Bam Margera]] destroying [[Vincent Margera|Don Vito's]] cars in \"Bamiature Golf\" and again in \"Where's Vito?\" during a retrospective for Bam's Hummer after it was thrown off the cliff by Vito. Enya performed the song at the [[2001 World Music Awards]].\n\nThe song's music video, which shows Enya performing the song in a spring, summer, fall and winter theme, was directed by [[Graham Fink]] and was released in 2000.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://enyaone.com/video-only-time.html|title=Only Time, 2000. Directed by Graham Fink |work=EnyaOne|year=2000|accessdate=2014-06-03}}</ref> In 2002, the song received an [[Echo Music Prize|ECHO Award]] for Best Single of the Year.\n\nOn November 13, 2013, the \"[[Epic Split]]\" advertisement was launched for the [[Volvo Trucks]] [[Volvo FM]] range and featured the song and [[Jean-Claude Van Damme]]. The success of the ad caused \"Only Time\" to re-enter the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 at number 43,<ref>{{cite web|last=Davies|first=Alex|title=Jean-Claude Van Damme Did A Crazy Split Standing On 2 Trucks For A Volvo Ad|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/jean-claude-van-damme-epic-split-volvo-trucks-2013-11|publisher=[[Business Insider]]|accessdate=27 November 2013|date=14 November 2013}}</ref><ref>http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5800854/lorde-royals-hot-100-chart-nine-weeks-eminem</ref> and the UK Singles Chart at number 95. [[Kraft Foods]] later used the song in advertisements showing parents relaxing while their kids eat [[Kraft Macaroni & Cheese]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://commercialsociety.wordpress.com/2019/04/07/those-kraft-mac-cheese-commercials-with-enyas-only-time/|work=Commercial Society|year=2019|accessdate=2019-06-22}}</ref>\n\n==Live performances==\nEnya performed \"Only Time\" several times, performances included ''[[Larry King Live]]'', ''[[Children in Need]]'', ''[[This Morning (TV programme)|This Morning]]'', ''[[The View (U.S. TV series)|The View]]'', ''Happy Xmas Show'', ''[[Entertainment Tonight]]'', ''[[Live with Kelly|Live! with Regis and Kelly]]'', ''[[The Tonight Show with Jay Leno]]'' and [[2001 World Music Awards]].\n\n==Track listings==\n'''2000 original release (single)'''\n# \"Only Time\"\n# \"The First of Autumn\"\n# \"The Promise\"\n\n'''2001 remix release (EP)'''\n# \"Only Time (S.A.F. remix)\"\n# \"O\u00edche Chi\u00fain\"\n# \"Willows on the Water\"\n# \"Only Time\"\n{{small|\"O\u00edche Chi\u00fan\" is properly spelled as \"O\u00edche Chi\u00fain\" on some editions.}}\n\n'''Promotional 2001 release'''\n# \"Only Time (S.A.F. pop radio remix)\"\n\n'''2004 reissue release'''\n# \"Only Time (S.A.F. pop radio remix)\"\n\n==Charts and sales==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Chart (2000\u20132002)\n!Peak<br>position\n|-\n|Australia ([[ARIA Charts|ARIA]])<ref>{{cite book|last=Ryan|first=Gavin|title=Australia's Music Charts 1988\u20132010|year=2011|publisher=Moonlight Publishing|location=Mt. Martha, VIC, Australia}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|69\n|-\n{{singlechart|Austria|2|artist=Enya|song=Only Time}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Wallonia Tip|11|artist=Enya|song=Only Time}}\n|-\n|Canada ([[Canadian Singles Chart|Nielsen SoundScan]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/enya/chart-history/CNS|title=Enya Chart History (Canadian Digital Songs)|publisher=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=30 May 2018}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|1\n|-\n|Europe ([[European Hot 100 Singles|Eurochart Hot 100]])<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/UK/Music-and-Media/00s/2001/MM-2001-10-20.pdf|title=Eurochart Hot 100 Singles|magazine=[[Music & Media]]|volume=18|issue=43|page=9|date=20 October 2001|access-date=9 February 2020}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|5\n|-\n{{singlechart|France|48|artist=Enya|song=Only Time}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Germany2|1|artist=Enya|song=Only Time|songid=4890}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Italy|17|artist=Enya|song=Only Time}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|